the land of Zebulun/Naphtali. These two lands are significant because Jesus dwelt in Capernaum, a city that was located "in the borders of Zabulon and Nephthalim" (Matt. 4:13). Jesus was the "great light" seen by the inhabitants of this area (9:2).
